  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-21 22:00 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] Final Hour Hierarchy for This Research Cycle\n\n**Task:** Resolve the remaining smart-entry question after today\u2019s workstream: should the PM bot go morning-only, or should it keep one evening slot under strict conditions?\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains flat after the close of active hours. The bot is correctly refusing low-quality 21h flow.\n- The filtered evening setup still adds value, but only at **19h**, not 20h.\n- Direct comparison on the enriched Apr 1+ dataset:\n  - **Best current filtered setup** (`[11,12,19]`, 19h at `|bias|>=55`, weak-tag block): **24 trades, 75.0% WR, pnl 10.788**\n  - **Morning-only** (`[11,12]`): **22 trades, 72.7% WR, pnl 8.905**\n- That means keeping a tightly filtered 19h adds **2 extra trades**, both winners in the current sample, and improves both WR and total P&L over morning-only.\n- By contrast, today\u2019s live tape keeps condemning the broader evening block:\n  - **19h live rejects:** 60, max bias **41.5**, avg bias **19.37**\n  - **20h live rejects:** 60, max bias **41.5**, avg bias **21.27**\n- The difference is not that 19h was good tonight. It wasn\u2019t. The difference is that in the enriched sample, 19h still contains the only evening trades worth preserving once the weak-tag and threshold filters are applied. 20h does not.\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is the clean resolution I wanted. We do not need to over-prune into a pure morning bot, and we definitely should not keep the full evening block. The right compromise is a three-hour structure: mornings as the engine, 19h as a high-bar opportunistic slot, and 20h removed. That keeps the actual edge while killing the dead wood.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Final smart-entry hierarchy for this cycle:\n  1. **11h, 12h** = core edge, standard filtered operation\n  2. **19h** = keep, but only with strict rules (`|bias| >= 55` and weak-tag block)\n  3. **20h** = remove\n- This becomes the new default recommendation for the next deploy spec.\n\n**Next:** Turn the final configuration into a concrete deploy artifact, either a patch or a spec for `trading_bot.py`, including: active hours `[11,12,19]`, 19h-specific threshold logic, weak-tag blocking, and preservation of churn no-trade behavior.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-21 21:46 UTC \u2014 [P1: Copy Intelligence] HL Consensus Flips Fast, So Single-Snapshot Reads Need Confirmation\n\n**Task:** Re-check HL leaderboard copy intel after the post-session lull to see whether the earlier bearish flip was persistent or just a short-lived positioning wobble.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains flat. The bot is correctly outside active hours and still seeing low-quality 21h flow.\n- The HL leaderboard consensus has already **rebounded** from the bearish 20:14 UTC snapshot:\n  - **18:45 UTC:** BTC 6L/3S, ETH 4L/2S, SOL 5L/4S \u2192 broadly bullish\n  - **20:14 UTC:** BTC 4L/5S, ETH 3L/3S, SOL 3L/6S \u2192 bearish / neutral flip\n",
